$values.Text: For all that NINA does well, it defines the periods in an odd way. For the dusks it defines the end of the period. For the dawns it defines the start of the period.
What nina calls sunset  is really is sunset); sunrise is really sunrise
what nina calls nautical dusk is the start of astronomical dusk (sun at -12 on the way down); nautical dawn is really nautical dawn (sun at -12 on the way up)
what nina calls astronomical dusk is the start of astronomical night  (sun at -18 on the way down); astronomical dawn is really astronomical dawn (sun at -18 on the way up)
